		div
			p Tables are a great way to lay out information that may otherwise be confusing, and can also make information a lot easier to compare. They can however be more difficult for people with accessibility needs, so it's important to only use them where they are needed.
			p Putting long form text into a table should generally be avoided.

			h2 Basic table
			p It's important to use the #[span.code th] tag and #[span.code scope] attribute when defining a table heading. This is for both styling and accessibility.
			.example-box-plain
				table
					thead
						tr
							th(scope="col") Column heading
							th(scope="col") Column heading
							th(scope="col") Column heading
					tbody
						tr
							td Table cell
							td Table cell
							td Table cell
						tr
							td Table cell
							td Table cell
							td Table cell
			pre
				code.language-html
					| &lt;table&gt;
					| 	&lt;thead&gt;
					| 		&lt;tr&gt;
					| 			&lt;th scope="col"&gt;Column heading&lt;/th&gt;
