			h2 Table with a footer
			p Footers on tables are useful in specific situations. This is easily defined with the #[code.code tfoot] tag. It's important to use this tag for styling and accessibility.
			p This example also shows right aligned cells, which is useful for numbers.
			.example-box-plain
				table
					thead
						tr
							th(scope="col", colspan="2") Budget table
					tbody
						tr
							td Label
							td.right £00.00
					tfoot
						tr
							td Total
							td.right £00.00
			pre
				code.language-html
					| &lt;table&gt;
					|	&lt;thead&gt;
					|		&lt;tr&gt;
					|			&lt;th scope="col" colspan="2"&gt;Budget table&lt;/th&gt;
					|		&lt;/tr&gt;
					|	&lt;/thead&gt;
					|	&lt;tbody&gt;
					|		&lt;tr&gt;
					|			&lt;td&gt;Label&lt;/td&gt;
